item.title: [HBASE-9368] TestDistributedLogSplitting.testDelayedDeleteOnFailure fails on occasion

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment: Sure. Let me take a look at this. Thanks.

Stack Good news is that testDelayedDeleteOnFailure didn't fail after all(it's stable now). The test failed at line 


   startCluster(1);

Basically we can't start minicluster. The top of call stack points that we can't start a thread. It seems due to some resource constraints on the build machine? Like # of files limit or not enough memory. Nicolas Liochon Have you seen this before? Thanks!


at java.lang.Thread.start0(Native Method)

at java.lang.Thread.start(Thread.java:640)
Resource constraint. Resolving. Thank you for looking Jeffrey Zhong (me happy TDLS fixed). Thanks for the persistence. I suppose could up timeout too.

I see this failing frequently in 0.94 with


java.lang.RuntimeException: null not an instance of org.apache.hadoop.hbase.MiniHBaseCluster

But there's no indication in the log that the start of the minicluster failures (that would be an explanation).
